            <h2>Conventional and trenchless sewer repair</h2>
            <p>Honest Drain offers two main approaches: <strong>conventional sewer repair</strong> using traditional excavation methods, and <strong>trenchless methods</strong> for minimally invasive repairs when pipe condition permits.</p>
            <h3>Conventional repair is best for:</h3>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>Tree root invasion with severe structural damage</li>
              <li>Pipe collapse or significant deterioration</li>
              <li>Severe blockages requiring mechanical removal</li>
              <li>Drainage issues requiring line repositioning</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="story-card">
            <strong>Common scope of work</strong>
            <ul class="pill-list"><li>Spot repair of broken sections</li><li>Full sewer replacement</li><li>Trenchless pipe relining</li><li>Pipe bursting replacement</li><li>Cleanout installation</li><li>Yard restoration coordination</li><li>Permitting and inspection support</li><li>Documentation for insurance</li></ul>
